bio_graph_0000050,"Inside a closed nutrient basin, there are 6 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, and F. researchers observed a directed nutrient-dependency network among six to ten species. The system obeys the following rules: each specie has directed outgoing interactions toward exactly 1 distinct others; each specie receives directed input from exactly 3 others; no organism interacts with itself; no directed interaction is reciprocated. Field observations additionally record that A draws nutrients from B; B draws nutrients from C; C draws nutrients from D; D draws nutrients from A; E draws nutrients from C; F draws nutrients from E. Determine whether a valid completion exists. If it does, provide one valid completion. If it does not, identify the contradiction.",0
bio_graph_0000079,"Inside an isolated forest micro-ecosystem, there are 7 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, and G.
the mature species interact through recurring predation links.

Biologists established the following rules:
- each specie preys on exactly 1 distinct others.
- each specie is targeted by exactly 3 others.
- no species preys on itself.
- the full ecosystem must be strongly connected.

Observed relationships:
- A preys on B.
- B preys on C.
- C preys on D.
- D preys on A.
- F preys on C.
- G preys on F.

Can the partial observations be extended to a full valid system? Give a witness if possible, otherwise prove impossibility.",0
bio_graph_0000170,"Within an isolated cave ecosystem, there are 8 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, G, and H. the adult population participates in a closed nutrient-exchange structure. The system obeys the following rules: each specie has directed outgoing interactions toward exactly 3 distinct others; each specie receives directed input from exactly 2 others; no organism interacts with itself; the full nutrient network must be strongly connected. Field observations additionally record that A draws nutrients from B; B draws nutrients from C; C draws nutrients from D; D draws nutrients from A; G draws nutrients from C; H draws nutrients from G. Can the partial observations be extended to a full valid system? Give a witness if possible, otherwise prove impossibility.",0
bio_graph_0000173,"Inside a closed nutrient basin, there are 7 species labeled A, B, C, D, E, F, and G. biologists modeled the colony as a directed nutrient-flow network. The system obeys the following rules: each specie has directed outgoing interactions toward exactly 3 distinct others; each specie receives directed input from exactly 2 others; no organism interacts with itself; the full nutrient network must be strongly connected; every species must lie on at least one directed cycle. Field observations additionally record that A draws nutrients from B; B draws nutrients from C; C draws nutrients from D; D draws nutrients from A; F draws nutrients from C; G draws nutrients from F. Can the partial observations be extended to a full valid system? Give a witness if possible, otherwise prove impossibility.",0
